          {
            "commit": "51f1b46dab6c2cc16f71d3f3be483f530b5e4001",
            "subject": "LU-8645 ptlrpc: update imp_known_replied_xid on resend-replay"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Fan Yong",
          "email": "fan.yong@intel.com",
          "date": "2016-06-17 03:20:39.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Oleg Drokin",
          "email": "oleg.drokin@intel.com",
          "date": "2016-10-20 10:36:03.000000000",
          "tz": 0
        },
        "subject": "LU-6635 lfsck: block replacing the OST-object for test",
        "message": "LU-6635 lfsck: block replacing the OST-object for test\n\nFor sanity-lfsck test_18e, sometimes, before the client wirte\nhappened, the layout LFSCK has already gone into the phase2\nand replaced the new created OST-object with the old orphan\nOST-object, then cause the subsequent check failure.\n\nTo resolve such trouble, we will hold the layout LFSCK when\nreplacing the new created OST-object until the client write\nhappened.\n\nSigned-off-by: Fan Yong <fan.yong@intel.com>\nChange-Id: Ia5be2cd2ea920fa02bb281ca5c59d8d252f3fd7b\nReviewed-on: http://review.whamcloud.com/18146\nTested-by: Jenkins\nTested-by: Maloo <hpdd-maloo@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Andreas Dilger <andreas.dilger@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Lai Siyao <lai.siyao@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <oleg.drokin@intel.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
